content:
Create a Job Profile

A job profile lets you describe the skill requirements that are needed for the work.

Workforce Engagement is available in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.
Shift Scheduling is available in the Contact Center SKU, Einstein 1 Service Edition, and Service Suites.

To view, create, and update shifts and job profiles:
View, create, and edit on Shifts, Job Profiles, Service Territories, Service Resources, Service Territory Memberships

When you set up Shift Scheduling or Workforce Engagement, create job profiles that represent the knowledge or expertise needed for the work.

From the App Launcher, open Job Profiles.
Click New.
Enter a name and description for the job profile.
Associate skills with the job profile.
Select the skills required for the job profile.
Map job profiles to queues in Workforce Engagement to determine staffing needs and schedule shifts based on queues.
title: Creating Job Profiles in Service Cloud
